<!-- Faq Section -->
<section id="faq" class="faq section light-background">
    <div class="container section-title" data-aos="fade-up">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-lg-10" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
                <div class="faq-container">
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <h3>What is a Hospital Management System (HMS)?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>A Hospital Management System (HMS) is a software platform that helps hospitals and healthcare facilities manage various aspects of their operations, including patient registration, appointment scheduling, billing, medical records, staff management, inventory, and more. It streamlines processes, improves efficiency, and enhances patient care.</p>
                        </div>
                        <i class="faq-toggle bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <h3>How does an HMS improve patient care?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>An HMS enhances patient care by providing quick access to accurate patient records, reducing errors in treatment plans, facilitating easier appointment scheduling, and improving communication between healthcare providers. This results in more informed decision-making and better patient outcomes.</p>
                        </div>
                        <i class="faq-toggle bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <h3>Is the Hospital Management System secure?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Yes, the HMS is designed with robust security measures to protect patient data. It includes features like data encryption, access control, audit logs, and compliance with healthcare regulations such as HIPAA and GDPR. Only authorized personnel have access to sensitive information.</p>
                        </div>
                        <i class="faq-toggle bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <h3>Can the HMS be accessed remotely?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Yes, the HMS can be accessed remotely by authorized users. It includes secure login portals for patients, doctors, and staff, allowing them to access relevant information and perform necessary actions from any location with internet connectivity.</p>
                        </div>
                        <i class="faq-toggle bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <h3>How does the HMS handle emergency cases?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>The HMS is equipped to handle emergency cases by allowing priority patient registration and admission. It can notify relevant healthcare providers and allocate resources such as beds, staff, and operation rooms for immediate treatment.</p>
                        </div>
                        <i class="faq-toggle bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <h3>Can I access my medical records online?</h3>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Yes, registered patients can access their electronic medical records (EMR) through the patient portal. Log in with your credentials, and you can view your medical history, lab reports, prescriptions, and treatment plans.</p>
                        </div>
                        <i class="faq-toggle bi bi-chevron-right"></i>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

